    <note type="biography">
        <p>American mathematician and philosopher. Calculator for the newly established <hi rend="italic">American ephemeris and nautical almanac</hi>, for which he devised new methods of calculation, 1852–72. Recording secretary, American Academy of Arts and Sciences, Boston, 1863–70. Published the first of a series of philosophical essays in the <hi rend="italic">North American Review</hi> in 1864.</p></note>
